## Improvement Intent

The performance issue is in the `matchingAcls` method where Scala's `Set ++` operation is used to combine multiple ACL sets. When the right-hand set has many entries (100+), this operation becomes slow due to iterating through all entries and calculating hash codes. Since `authorize` is called for every request to the broker, this performance issue is critical.

The solution replaces the inefficient `prefixed ++ wildcard ++ literal` chain with a single `mutable.HashSet` that accumulates all ACLs, then converts to an immutable Set. This avoids the repeated hash code calculations and intermediate Set creations.

## Changes

